{
  "texts": [
    "These polymers were generated from monomers selected based on polymerizability and molecular weight criteria and further polymerized to have at least 150 heavy atoms in their backbone.",
    "We performed MD simulations on polymer-Li +.TFSI -systems at 353 K with a salt molality of 1.5 mol/kg using the Large Atomic Molecular Massively Parallel Simulator (LAMMPS) 75, with the Polymer Consistent Forcefield (PCFF+) 57.",
    "The workflow included the generation of amorphous polymer structures, relaxation, and equilibration phases, followed by a production run to calculate ion transport properties like ionic conductivity.",
    "The equilibration phase involved sequential NVT (constant number of particles, volume, and temperature) and NPT (constant number of particles, pressure, and temperature) ensembles to adjust the system to densities close to theoretical predictions.",
    "The production run was performed under NVT conditions at 353 K for 5 ns with a time step of 2.0 fs."
  ]
}